The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The use of matroids suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves optimization and approximation algorithms, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with budget constraints and valuations, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT).
